# API Reference

This document provides a reference for the API endpoints and includes examples of `curl` commands for each endpoint.

## Users

### Get all users

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/users`

### Create a new user

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name": "testuser", "email": "test@user.com"}' http://localhost:8080/api/users`

## Artist Profiles

### Get all artist profiles

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/artists`

### Create a new artist profile

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"userId": 1, "bio": "A test artist", "location": "Testland"}' http://localhost:8080/api/artists`

## Proposals

### Get all proposals

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/proposals`

### Create a new proposal

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title": "Test Proposal", "description": "This is a test proposal", "creatorId": 1}' http://localhost:8080/api/proposals`

## Marketplace Items

### Get all marketplace items

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/marketplace-items`

### Create a new marketplace item

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"title": "Test Item", "description": "This is a test item", "price": 9.99}' http://localhost:8080/api/marketplace-items`

## Moderation Cases

### Get all moderation cases

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/moderation-cases`

### Create a new moderation case

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"userId": 1, "reason": "Test case"}' http://localhost:8080/api/moderation-cases`

## Transactions

### Get all transactions

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/transactions`

### Create a new transaction

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"userId": 1, "amount": 100, "description": "Test transaction"}' http://localhost:8080/api/transactions`

## Support Tickets

### Get all support tickets

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/support-tickets`

### Create a new support ticket

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"userId": 1, "subject": "Test Ticket", "description": "This is a test ticket"}' http://localhost:8080/api/support-tickets`

## Forum Threads

### Get all forum threads

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/forum-threads`

### Create a new forum thread

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"authorId": 1, "title": "Test Thread", "body": "This is a test thread"}' http://localhost:8080/api/forum-threads`

## Treasury Assets

### Get all treasury assets

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/treasury-assets`

### Create a new treasury asset

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name": "Test Asset", "balance": 1000}' http://localhost:8080/api/treasury-assets`

## Staff Members

### Get all staff members

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/staff-members`

### Create a new staff member

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"name": "Test Staff", "role": "Tester"}' http://localhost:8080/api/staff-members`

## Equity Opportunities

### Get all equity opportunities

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/equity-opportunities`

### Create a new equity opportunity

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"artistProfileId": 1, "title": "Test Opportunity", "description": "This is a test opportunity."}' http://localhost:8080/api/equity-opportunities`

## Lead Queries

### Get all lead queries

`curl http://localhost:8080/api/lead-queries`

### Create a new lead query

`curl -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" -d '{"artistProfileId": 1, "query": "Test Query"}' http://localhost:8080/api/lead-queries`
